In his weekly address, President Trump expressed a new sense of optimism in the country, stating that power is being returned from Washington to the American people. He emphasized his commitment to putting American workers first and fighting for their interests. The President signed an executive order in Kenosha, Wisconsin, to Buy American and Hire American, ensuring that federal projects are made with American goods and that American workers and companies are not cheated out of contracts. He also mentioned taking action to reform the immigration system to prioritize the needs of American workers. The President highlighted the importance of honoring work and craftsmanship, stating that the work of skilled tradespeople is just as noble as that of doctors, CEOs, and politicians. By making government answer to the citizens, the President believes that the limits on the country's future will be removed, allowing for the growth and strength of America.